@database psbook.guide

@width 72

@node main "psbook.guide"

PSUtils Release 1 Patchlevel 16

NAME

psbook - rearrange pages in PostScript file into signatures


SYNOPSIS

@{b}psbook@{ub} [@{b}-q@{ub}] [@{b}-s@{ub}@{i}signature@{ui}] [@{i}infile [@{i}outfile] ]

@{i}`Online help' :@{ui} @{b} psbook -?@{ub}

DESCRIPTION

@{i}Psbook@{ui} rearranges pages from a PostScript document into ``signatures'' for
printing books or booklets, creating a new PostScript file. The
input PostScript file should follow the Adobe Document Structuring
Conventions.

The @{b}-s@{ub} option selects the size of signature which will be used.
The signature size is the number of sides which will be folded and bound
together; the number given should be a multiple of four. The default is
to use one signature for the whole file. Extra blank sides will be added
if the file does not contain a multiple of four pages.

Psbook normally prints the page numbers of the pages rearranged; the
@{b}-q@{ub} option suppresses this.


